One hot encoding of features and training decision tree¶

In [3]:
dtclf = DecisionTreeClassifier(criterion='entropy',splitter='best',random_state=0)
one_hot_data = pd.get_dummies(df[['Color','WeightGms']],drop_first=True)
display(one_hot_data)
dtclf.fit(one_hot_data, df['Fruit'])

Visualizing the created tree¶

feaName = ['WeightGms','Color_Orange','Color_Red','Color_Yellow']
cn=['Apple','Grape','Orange','Strawberry'] #Should be given in ascending order
fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows = 1,ncols = 1,figsize = (8,8), dpi=100)
plot_tree(dtclf,feature_names = feaName, class_names=cn,filled = True)

Understanding Entropy Calculation¶

Entropy = $\sum_{i=1}^{c} (-p_ilog_2(p_i))$

Top Level : Apple:4 , Grape:2 , Orange:4 , Strawberry:4
Probabilities: Apple:4/14 , Grape:2/14 , Orange:4/14 , Strawberry:4/14
$-\frac{4}{14}log_2(\frac{4}{14}) -\frac{2}{14}log_2(\frac{2}{14}) -\frac{4}{14}log_2(\frac{4}{14}) -\frac{4}{14}log_2(\frac{4}{14})$

Making prediction on Test Data¶

In [11]:
dfx = pd.read_csv('TestData.csv')
display(dfx)
one_hot_datax = pd.get_dummies(dfx[['Color','WeightGms']],drop_first=True)
display(one_hot_datax)
one_hot_datax['Color_Yellow'] = 0
display(one_hot_datax)
Yp = dtclf.predict(one_hot_datax)
dfx['Fruit'] = list(Yp)
display(dfx)
